<item>
            <title>[MATH-1070] Incorrect rounding of float</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/MATH-1070</link>
                <project id="12310485" key="MATH">Commons Math</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;package org.apache.commons.math3.util &lt;br/&gt;
example of usage of round functions of Precision class:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Precision.round(0.0f, 2, BigDecimal.ROUND_UP) = 0.01&lt;br/&gt;
Precision.round((float)0.0, 2, BigDecimal.ROUND_UP) = 0.01&lt;br/&gt;
Precision.round((float) 0.0, 2) = 0.0&lt;br/&gt;
Precision.round(0.0, 2, BigDecimal.ROUND_UP) = 0.0&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Seems the reason is usage of extending float to double inside round functions and getting influence of memory trash as value.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I think, same problem will be found at usage of other round modes.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>&lt;p&gt;Windows 7, IntelliJ IDEA 10.5.4.&lt;/p&gt;</environment>
